# Dart-throwing robot (CMU 16-745 SPEC)

Single installable Python package **`dartrobot`** (motion → flight → integration → optional RL). Legacy `physics/` and duplicate phase folders were removed; use this README and [`HIGH_LEVEL_CONTROL_STRATEGY.md`](HIGH_LEVEL_CONTROL_STRATEGY.md) as the entry points.

## Quickstart

```bash
cd Projecto   # repo root
python3 -m venv .venv && source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -e ".[rl]"          # core + optional SB3 / Gymnasium
dartrobot --help
dartrobot mc --preset t10 --n 50 --seed 0
dartrobot demo --quick
pytest tests/motion/regression_suite.py -q
```

Install core only (no RL): `pip install -e .`

## Layout

```mermaid
flowchart TB
  subgraph pkg [src/dartrobot]
    motion[motion MJCF plus controller]
    flight[flight integrator scoring]
    integration[integration pipeline optimizers]
    rl[rl env train eval]
    spin[spin ablation]
    mc[mc scatter plots]
    demo[demo plus showcase HTML]
  end
  tests[tests motion flight integration]
  artifacts[artifacts generated PNG JSON manifests]
  policies[policies SB3 checkpoints pickle caches]
  pkg --> artifacts
  rl --> policies
  tests --> pkg
```

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| [`src/dartrobot/`](src/dartrobot/) | Library code (`constants`, `motion`, `flight`, `integration`, `rl`, `spin`, `mc`, `demo`) |
| [`tests/`](tests/) | Former `VALIDATION_*` scripts; runnable with `pytest` |
| [`artifacts/`](artifacts/) | Generated plots, manifests, baseline cache (`artifacts/baseline/`) |
| [`policies/`](policies/) | SB3 `.zip` and `warm_start_cache.pkl` |
| [`archive/presentation/`](archive/presentation/) | Slides PDF and demo media (not required for code) |

## CLI (`dartrobot`)

| Subcommand | Purpose |
|------------|---------|
| `dartrobot demo` | Run flight + motion (+ optional C1) validations, then build HTML showcase |
| `dartrobot mc` | Target-score Monte Carlo; optional `--optimize-knots`, `--use-baseline-cache` |
| `dartrobot baseline` | Build strong classical baseline cache (knots + release time grid) |
| `dartrobot debug` | Stage-by-stage throw pipeline diagnostics |
| `dartrobot rl-train` | PPO residual training (requires `[rl]` extra) |
| `dartrobot rl-eval` | Evaluate a saved policy at one target |

See `--help` on each subcommand for full arguments.

## RL

See [`src/dartrobot/rl/README.md`](src/dartrobot/rl/README.md) (migrated from the old `README_RL_SPEC`). Default warm-start cache: `artifacts/baseline/strong_baseline_cache.pkl`, with fallback to `policies/warm_start_cache.pkl`.

## Assignment context (short)

Course deliverable: **4-DOF** arm (shoulder yaw + three sagittal hinges), MuJoCo spline+PD throws, analytic flight to the board plane **x = 2.37 m**, B3 scoring, integration robustness and optional residual RL. Constants match **`dart_robot_tasklist.pdf`** via [`src/dartrobot/constants.py`](src/dartrobot/constants.py).

## Overhand kinematics (short)

The arm uses a **shoulder yaw** (world +z) then a **pitch chain** in the sagittal plane; release state is read from MuJoCo `release_site` and passed to the ballistic model. Details live in docstrings under `dartrobot.motion` and in [`HIGH_LEVEL_CONTROL_STRATEGY.md`](HIGH_LEVEL_CONTROL_STRATEGY.md).

## Known limits

- Jacobian linearization is local; re-run readiness tests after major retunes.
- RL env is one-step residual-on-warm-start; full closed-loop training is future work.

